        </author>
    </info>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>I had to find this for my Surface 4 computer, which isn't that same as my Surface 2
            Pro.</para>
        <figure pgwide="0">
            <title>01 Fn-Win-Space</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="01%20Fn-Win-Space.png" scalefit="1"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Choose the Stanford Visitor access point to avoid the 4 hour limit on the Stanford
            access point.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>02 Stanford Visitor</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="02%20Stanford%20Visitor.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Accept the Terms and Conditions.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>03 Wireless Visitor</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="03%20Wireless%20Visitor.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>You should now be connected and you can close this window.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>04 You're Connected</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="04%20You%27re%20Connected.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Start up the Droid Cam Client that will communicate with my Android phone's
            camera.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>05 DroidCam Client</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="05%20DroidCam%20Client.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Tell it to start up the wired USB connection, to avoid any additional wireless
            traffic.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>06 DroidCam Client USB</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="06%20DroidCam%20Client%20USB.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>This gives you the 1st preview of the camera's viewing angle. Using the X Pro version
            give more resolution.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>07 DroidCamX Pro Controls</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="07%20DroidCamX%20Pro%20Controls.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Start up the Many Cam app that will communicate with Google Hangouts. Originally, the
            was required for compatibility with the Hangout, but it might be just an extra step, at
            this point. Still, the extra camera controll and effects might also be useful, some
            day.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>08%20ManyCam.png</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="08%20ManyCam.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>I have all of my cameras turned on, but "cut" over to the DroidCam, almost all of the
            time.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>09 ManyCam Controls</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="09%20ManyCam%20Controls.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Open a web browser (I use Chrome) to Google plus.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>10 plus.google.com</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="10%20plus.google.com.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Switch over to the SVFIG account, rather than my personal one, so the announcement
            comes out from that organization.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>11 Silicon Valley Forth Interest Group</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="11%20Silicon%20Valley%20Forth%20Interest%20Group.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Pull down the Google+ Page tab.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>12 SVFIG Google Plus</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="12%20SVFIG%20Google%20Plus.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>And select Hangouts.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>13 Google Hangouts</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="13%20Google%20Hangouts.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Select the Hangouts On Air tab.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>14 Hangouts On Air</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="14%20Hangouts%20On%20Air.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Hit the Create a Hangout On Air button.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>15 Create a Hangout On Air</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="15%20Create%20a%20Hangout%20On%20Air.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Give the hangout an appropriate name, so people can find it on YouTube.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>16 SVFIG 23Apr2016 Morning</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="16%20SVFIG%2023Apr2016%20Morning.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>The online annoncement for the even is now created. Press the Start button.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>17 SVFIG 23Apr2016 Start</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="17%20SVFIG%2023Apr2016%20Start.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>If this is the 1st time on this machine, Windows may ask for permission to turn on the
            webcam.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>18 Allow Webcam</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="18%20Allow%20Webcam.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>You can invite guests now, or add them later. We typically, only do this for remote
            speakers.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>19 Invite Guests</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="19%20Invite%20Guests.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>If you are early, you can just wait here until it gets close to the time for the
            hangout to start. However, be aware that it takes a little bit of time to actually get
            the broadcast started, so don't cut it too short.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>20 Start Broadcast</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="20%20Start%20Broadcast.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>I have to admit, that I chose wrong here, but fixed it later. You should select the
            ManyCam Virtual Webcam, instead of the DroidCam Source 1 that is highlighted.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>21 Camera Settings</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="21%20Camera%20Settings.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Now you can adjust the camera angle. Typically, our focus is on the screen, but
            sometimes, we do pan around.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>22 Camera Angle</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="22%20Camera%20Angle.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Down at the bottom right, select the Links button.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>23 YouTube Page</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="23%20YouTube%20Page.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Copy the YouTube Page for the email announcement.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>24 YouTube Page Selected</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="24%20YouTube%20Page%20Selected.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>I should have figured out how to eliminate this section, but didn't.</para>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Send email with the pertenant information to the mailing list.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>26 SVFIG Email</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="26%20SVFIG%20Email.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Both DroidCam and ManyCam can control zoom, but I use ManyCam for this.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>27 ManyCam Zoom</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="27%20ManyCam%20Zoom.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Yet another duplicate.</para>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>Even worse, two blank sections.</para>
    </sect1>
    <sect1>
        <title/>
        <para/>
        <para>The last setting is merely to get the broadcast up to scale.</para>
        <figure>
            <title>30 ManyCam 1080p</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="30%20ManyCam%201080p.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </sect1>
</article>
